text:
the future is female...and male. as a woman with brothers + nephews and i‚Äôve got to be honest and speak up with the #unpopularopinion. i don‚Äôt like this new #ibelievewomen movement. i believe this new narrative where we say we believe women  instantly implies that men are the enemy. they‚Äôre lying, hiding something and are surely the perpetrators.  there is no gender exclusivity for assault. we shouldn‚Äôt contribute to a narrative where we invalidate men. their innocence, their assault. i don‚Äôt want my children growing up thinking men are the enemy. i just don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs fair. sure, there are cases in which it‚Äôs true, where there are facts and evidence and people need to pay the price for their crimes but let‚Äôs be sure to acknowledge (& include) that men are also the victims in some situations. that there are women out there doing the unthinkable too. that men too, can be innocent. they can be survivors. we are all about #womanempowerment but we‚Äôve got to be responsible for the negative narrative we create on the way. let‚Äôs acknowledge the casey anthonys of the world. do you ‚Äúbelieve‚Äù her? there are survivors. .
.
we believe #them .
we believe #survivors. .
.
nothing else. .
.
#metoo #ibelievewomen #kavanaugh #ibelieveher #letsbereal #honesty #radicalfeminism

text:
tw: when i was 12, the older brother of an old friend of mine sexually assaulted me. not long after, we stopped being friends. i didn't tell anyone because he said he'd tell all his friends about what happened, and as a scared 12 year old, i believed him. that same year that friends mother had a boyfriend who would touch me in the pool when we went swimming, i never said anything because i would've been called a liar, just like i was when i told my friend about it. when i was 15, a friend of mine offered to pay me for sex. i declined, and the next monday morning i found out he told all our guy friends about it. when i tried to speak up and defend myself by talking about it to a friend, i was told to stop because i could 'ruin his life'. when i was 16, a boy sexually assaulted me without even knowing. if you have to beg a person for sex to the point where they say yes just to make you leave them alone, that's sexual assault.  now, i'd never press charges against any of these people because i don't consider myself a survivor of rape or sexual assault. and i'm only coming out with this now because we have voted a rapist into office, and we're doing the same thing with brett kavanaugh. brock turners turn into brett kavanaughs who then make rules for brock turners. stand up, speak out. don't let toxic men run our country. 
#metoo

text:
this week. i know you are feeling it too. between what is happening in the world and what has been going on personally, i have shed far too many tears this week. i am exhausted emotionally and physically. (see the bags under my eyes? yikes!) and now, despite my best effort to shield them, my sweet girls are starting to pick up on the trauma. ‚Ä¢

we talk a lot about what it means to be a girl and how to be strong and how to protect ourselves from tricky people. they listen and absorb whatever they can. i do my very best to be a good role model to them. ‚Ä¢

this week alone i have been talked down to (mansplained) because of my gender, lied to because it is assumed i don‚Äôt know better (surprise, i do.), and i was forced into a very uncomfortable situation after a medical professional decided that they didn‚Äôt need consent before touching me. and this is normal. this isn‚Äôt a one-off week. this is the life of an average woman. (and our trans sisters face even further trauma.) ‚Ä¢

we have to do better. i am angry. this is not a scary time for men, it is an awakening to how incredibly terrifying it has always been to be a woman. it is time for our male allies to step up and do some serious work with their brothers. the sisterhood is pissed and we are done carrying this burden any longer.

text:
when did the misuse of sexual power start? when did women fell off their natural state of standing beside men. equally. beautifully united. in love. it started a long time ago. back in egypt. when the priests decided that they don‚Äòt need the goddess anymore. because it was hard to control her. make her submissive and make her obey their rules. so they kicked her off her throne and put one god there. a male one. this was the beginning of religion ruled by male gods. and they started to sexually abuse women in magic rituals to get spiritual power. it is called sex magic. revived by aleister crowley who misused the spiritual concept of tantra to reduce it to sex. 
but we have to remember that it is the woman who carries the mysteries of life. it is her who can nourish life and we do desperately need men who see the goddess in us without wanting to control her. this is a story that still has to be written because it is her story. and in the last two decades of his-story there was no place for the goddess. so what is really making me furious: it is still happening. especially in the spiritual scene where some think they are gods and gods in bed misusing a bunch of women with their spiritual love talking. watch out dear sisters. listen deeply to your intuition before you open your temple. and ask yourself does the love come from the heart or from the sexual longing that can so easily be misused in patriarchal power structures. so many think they are gods. but if they don‚Äôt learn to respect and come back into their hearts then they are nothing more than small men of power. and this is something that has to stop. now. i am working in sacred women‚Äôs circles. holding space for the healing. we have to transform the structures of power held in sexuality so we can rise into the heart. and it starts with you. and you. and you. tag a woman if you feel that she needs this message. from soul to soul. and tag men you think they should read this. 
#womencircle #venusretrograde #sexualabuse #risesisterrise #magic #sexmagic #tantra #priestesspath #awakeningmasculine #awakeningfeminine #metoo

text:
every time i see a post, a tweet, a blog, a comment, a news article about a woman who is been  bashed for coming forward and speaking up about sexual abuse, my heart bleeds.

it bleeds because i know their pain, i have lived their pain, i know their struggles. i know what it feels like to not be believed, i know what it feels like to be blamed/ to blame yourself for being a victim.

i am tired of people blaming survivors and questioning them for their timing.  instead of asking why now, the question should be why not now.

rape/sexual abuse and harassment is wrong, whenever a woman comes forward she should be listened to and not blamed for speaking her truth.

#believesurvivors #metoo #blametherapist #notorape

text:
happy wednesday all. i just want to stop and take a moment to discuss the kavanaugh nomination. you cannot believe dr. ford and judge kavanaugh at once. people say that because the attack was so long ago, she can't possibly remember the details. trust me, you never forget something like that. the ghost may become easier to live with, but it is always there. when is it ok to believe women for all we endure? when are we going to stop the controlling behavior and listen to what's really happening? i carry protection on me at all times to ensure that i'm as safe as i can be. why can i not trust men to keep their hands off? think about that, then think about the issue of abortion. it's not your body, it's not your choice. what we do for our bodies is no one's business. no one else should have a say in that especially an accused assailant. ¬∞
¬∞

text:
throwback to a project i did in 2014. 
it was focused around being an indian girl and expectations placed on us from the moment we're born. it dealt with the inequality we face due to the patriarchal structure and hierarchy that has been created over a long period of time. it also dealt with the violence and sexual abuse faced.

this was four years ago and yet the same discussion is going around today, in a much much larger contextü§î. wonder how long we're going to have to fight to be considered  and respected as an individual. 
thankful and grateful for the #metoo campaign that has transformed the way sexual abuse is signified. there's hope, there's changes but there's a long way to go! ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
self portrait: july 2014. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#deepalimalde #metoo #metoomvmt

text:
dear friend, 
it is not you fault.
you deserve respect always,
and to be assaulted never.
what you wore or how much alcohol your drank is not the reason, ever.
your past actions are not an excuse or karma and you did not deserve this.
you did nothing wrong & you should not feel ashamed by this.
‚Ä¢
the person that harmed you is at fault, they don't deserve or respect you.they used what you wore and how much you drank as a way for them to sleep at night. their past actions have everything to do with why they are creating this mayhem. they did everything wrong. they should feel ashamed, those fucking fucks.
‚Ä¢
however, i am here. and now you know.i will stand by you, i will stand up for you.i will fight for you, i will cry with you.i will never let you feel alone again. because just like this tragic event(s) that's happened to you,
it's happened to #metoo
‚Ä¢
this is the end of my latest blog. click the link in my bio to read the beginning. every story has a start & every voice needs to be heard. my bff @marcyharrisortizphotog gave me the courage to start sharing my own story, and i realize just like everything else i am so open and transparent about, that this should be no different
‚Ä¢

text:
i just read an article about how girls don't tell their fathers about their sexual assaults and i cried through the whole thing. i'm crying now.

i've never told my father nor my brother about any of my assaults. i didnt tell them about the first one on my tenth birthday. i certainly didn't tell them about the one in college. and i didn't mention all of the smaller things either. the guy who tried to corner me in an elevator. the guy who tried to grope me on the dance floor. the boss who always tried to sit so his leg was touching mine and told me how sexy i was.

i told my mom. and she told me not to tell anyone else. "just avoid them." in her way, she was trying to protect me, but i know now that silence only protects the attackers.

at 39, the thought of talking to my father and brother about this terrifies me. it makes me sick to my stomach. 
i worry they won't believe me. i worry they'll be hurt. i worry that it'll be too much. i worry that our relationship will be changed forever no matter what their reaction. 
but i have told my son. and we've talked a lot about consent and respect. and last week when he saw a girl being harassed on the bus he spoke up and the boy stopped and moved away from the girl.

so women, if you can't tell your fathers, please, please, for all the daughters - tell your sons.

text:
trump: "think of your sons!" likely worst case scenario for your son is that he doesn't get a job after being falsely accused (and he'd probably still get the job)

likely worst case scenario for your daughter is that she's chased by a maniac while jogging at night and while she's fumbling with her keys to open the car door she is grabbed, kidnapped, tied up, gagged, raped, beaten, mutilated, tortured, murdered and dumped somewhere in a ditch to rot cold and alone.

which do you think happens more often? there is an epidemic in this country and it's not of false accusations.

it makes me sick that in we live in a culture where sexual violence against women is so fucking normalized in tv shows, movies and stories on the news that it's completely ignored until the men who perpetuate this epidemic run the risk of being "falsely accused"

is it just normal now the only people we ever hear about or see being chased in the woods, kidnapped, tied up, stalked, raped or murdered are 99% of the time... women?

text:
as i watch the brett kavanaugh hearing unfold, my heart sinks down to my stomach as i witness a brave citizen relive her trauma to a room full of people, all of which are ill informed and not equipped to have a such a dialogue about sexual abuse. putting her testimony aside, the fact that both republicans and democrats are using her assault as a tool to either deny or confirm the naming of brett kavanaugh as our new supreme court judge shows the divisive and at times appalling nature of politics. the truth is, it doesn‚Äôt matter when ford would have come forward with her story, whether it be today or 10 years ago, people would still find some reason to victim blame her. comprehensive sex education is not widely provided in school, our country doesn‚Äôt teach consent in and out of the classroom, resulting in a huge lack of knowledge and understanding on these issues. we aren‚Äôt taught how to have healthy sexual relationships, it‚Äôs no wonder that we are witnessing such a tragic product of this culture. in no way am i defending kavanaugh but he and ford are a both a product of a culture that doesn‚Äôt believe survivors, doesn‚Äôt make consent a priority, and doesn‚Äôt hold sexual assaulters accountable for their actions. 
i do believe that people are becoming more aware of these issues everyday and although there is a long way to go before we can live in a world where woman don‚Äôt have to watch their drinks at bars, can control their own bodies, have access to paid maternity leave, and can walk home at night without fear of being attacked, i know there are a lot of people out there who are working so fucking hard to create change. don‚Äôt let this hearing make you believe people out there aren‚Äôt fighting the good fight. ‚úäüèΩüåà‚ú®üíô i wrote this song about street harassment after the news of trump ‚Äúgrabbing pussies‚Äù tape came out and it still rings true today and the more i think about it, the more i realize one of my tools as a songwriter is about speaking my truth. also humor helps too.

go listen to the full video link in my bio. thanks for reading. üôèüèΩ #consent #matters #listentowomen #music #originalsong #sexeducation #singersongwriter #tish__music

text:
today i went to a book launch of a woman and feminist i adore, clementine ford with one of my best friends. it‚Äôs prompted me to share this today. perhaps you‚Äôve wondered why i regularly share a lot of anti rape movements and content on my stories. 
this is me age 22. the same year i was sexually assaulted, four times, on four different accounts, by four different men. i knew these ‚Äòmen‚Äô, they were men i thought were my friends. 
in australia, 1 in 5 women have reported sexual assault. most of these perpetrators are people that these women know. these women could very well be your wives, girlfriends, sisters, mothers, daughters. 
eve ensler said something that really resonated with how i feel. ‚Äò i am fucking tired of the passivity of ‚Äògood men‚Äô. where the hell are you? you live with us, make love with us, get nurtured and mothered by us, father us, befriend us, and are eternally supported by us, so why aren‚Äôt you standing with us? why aren‚Äôt you driven to the point of madness and action by the brutality of rape and humiliation of us?‚Äô. i am tired of men who remain passive, and claim to be the ally of women i know, sitting on their arses with the privilege of male gender, doing fuck all, or wanting reward for basic human decency, or remaining ‚Äòneutral‚Äô or ‚Äòuninvolved‚Äô. sidrah may says, ‚Äòi want you to be traitors to the system that violently holds you up at the expense of women. i want you to betray the silent pack that patriarchy makes with you to have your back so long as you don‚Äôt make waves. revolt!‚Äô. it is not enough anymore to simply not be a perpetrator. i am tired of having this conversation, and of people who refuse to recognise the pervasiveness and seriousness of toxic masculinity culture, and the life long implications this and its subsequent behaviours can have on women. women who have been forced to remain silent due to a system that doesn‚Äôt support their voices. rape culture has succeeded in convincing us that rapists don‚Äôt look like men you know, and therefore the men you know could never actually be rapists. but guess what, they can be, and they are.
i will not stop. 
what are you actually doing to revolt?

text: this has been a hard week. i‚Äôm not even speaking for myself. i‚Äôm speaking on behalf of america. for those who have dared to stand up for the violence against them and those who have been left feeling ‚Äúwell no shit i didn‚Äôt report.‚Äù i stand in both of those places with the physical and sexual violence taken out on me. ive reported and was coerced into taking it back, because my assailant was a family member high up in the military who was in control of my brother. my dad told me he would have him killed in afghanistan. he was probably protecting himself from the abuse not only i was under for years, but cousins according to an aunt, now that i can rationally look back years later. i‚Äôve reported and even after detectives told me to say such degrading things during a recorded phone call, it went no where. the guy is living in london working in film still i assume. i‚Äôve not reported because it would have torn my family to pieces. it did anyway once my step mom read my journal and shared it with everyone. this country is ran by a president who has boasted and bragged about how he has the ability to get away with assaulting women because of who he is, on camera nonetheless. i haven‚Äôt slept several nights this week because of everything going on in our country, let alone what‚Äôs going on in my own life. i stand with dr. ford. she deserves respect. she is someone i wish i could be ‚Äî showing my face and speaking my truth.  the last couple of weeks have been really interesting in terms of prolonged exposure therapy. last week in our recording session i was so in my emotions it honestly scared me. i see a few followers who do actually know me. i have spoken about my abuse and assaults with little emotion. that wasn‚Äôt the case a week and a half ago. i was crying, hyperventilating, a shit show. it was so brutal to listen to each day afterwards. however, i said words i hate saying (this former wannabe doctor can‚Äôt say human anatomy for the life of her), and i said everything that happened in that event. this last monday i tapped into all the emotions i was feeling, which i‚Äôd done before but not as much. continued in comments. #metoo #prolongedexposuretherapy

text: women are still being killed around the world for expressing themselves and living their lives as they choose. we are not separate from these women, we may live in a different country, under a different government or a different religion, but we are them and they are us. the feminine (not only women but the aspects of the femme within all) is still being suppressed and disrespected. let‚Äôs allow men to grow their hair - in all institutions, if they wish, let‚Äôs allow women to be fully heard in their feelings and respected for those feelings as they would be respected for presenting a fact. let‚Äôs allow everyone to dance and express themselves, paint their faces and be given the time and respect to do these things as they would be given the time and respect if they were studying or ‚Äòachieving‚Äô some linear goal. sex too! let‚Äôs enjoy the process rather than going for the goal! we would all be full of joy if the balance was restored.#joy #femme #feminist #masculine #feminine #rebalance #goal #postmetoo #metoo #respect #letsdothiswitches

text:
no matter how we fight....
it changes you....
sometimes in ways you wish.....
could be different...
it awakens parts of a child that should not be...
no matter what, it was never your fault....
no matter what they said while hurting you.....
you were never a bad girl/boy....
there was nothing you could do....
there was nothing you could say....
laying still probably, surely saved you life....
your body was only allowed three choices from your mind to keep you safe....
fight, flight or freeze......
most of us chose freeze.....
we were terrified...
we were threaten to never tell....
so we froze while we were broken open 
inside and everything changed.

#itwasneveryourfault
#youarebeautiful
#sexualabuseisreal
#seekhelptoworkthroughit
#youareneveralone
#metoo

text:
#youneedtocutit series: cut those attachments to the projections that have been placed upon you: that your worth, your potential is dictated by your container (their projections). you define you. [2/5]
‚úÇÔ∏è
you were born perfect. a perfect seed full of potential; to grow, receive water, sun, air, love and life. some sprouts deprived of air, of sun, of a sturdy container, of safety. grown differently, feeling as if you were born faulty.
üí´
nothing, and i say nothing, was ever wrong with you, it was the confinement in which you've been held, the constant tearing of your roots, the deprivation of clean air, sun, love, and nourishment. it was never you, it was the world.
üí´
now rise to your potential. release that pain, that anger, the resentment that has been fed to you to condition you to destroy yourself from the inside out. rise above their standards, their unworthy expectations and unjust projections of you. reclaim your worth, your value, your ability to succeed despite these adversities.
üí´
from these ashes you shall rise.
.
.
.

text:
two ethics complaints have been filed against brett kavanaugh in the u.s. court of appeals for the d.c. circuit court on which he sits. as of this writing, those two complaints are being administered by the circuit court‚Äôs chief judge and previously defeated supreme court nominee merrick garland. 
kavanaugh is likely to face ethical questions despite the disposition of those two official complaints due to his partisan attacks against democrats, ‚Äúthe clintons‚Äù and other liberal groups when he alleged a vast, left-wing conspiracy against him during testimony in front of the senate judiciary committee last week. 
according to media reports‚Äô zoe tillman,¬†one of those official complaints concerns an allegation that kavanaugh ‚Äúlied about the sexual assault allegations against him.‚Äù the other complaint deals with allegations that kavanaugh lied before the senate judiciary committee when he testified during his initial confirmation hearing that he didn‚Äôt know he received and worked off of a treasure trove of documents stolen by a gop operative from senate democrats during his time with the administration of george w. bush.

so when artemisia paints herself, she not only portrays herself as a woman, the abused woman who took down a kingdom, she paints herself as a force of nature in the moment just before she‚Äôs about to stab herself with the dagger, looking up, looking fierce. no victims here. take that beyonce, this is what fierce looked like 400 years ago. 
works of this quality and mastery are in museums. this stunner belongs in a museum. and yet, it‚Äôs hanging on my office wall for you all to see today and tomorrow. üåü
oh, and it can be yours for ‚Ç¨500,000-700,000. with prices that will exchange hands in london this week for works that have not stood this test of time, it puts this masterpiece into context. boom! üí•

text:
long #metoo rant ahead.  this graphic has been around for a while and is loosely representative of the number of rapes that have or have not been reported, rapists who then have faced trial, been jailed, or those that have been falsely accused. the information came from multiple different studies and paints an interesting picture, doesn't it?  ever since the #metoo movement has picked up real steam there has been alot of big name celebrities who have been hit with sexual assault allegations. the movement has helped people stand up to their assaulters and invoke real change. this is amazing and a great stride forward for everyone, right? yet one look at this graphic and it's frightening to think that one of the biggest counter points i've heard about #metoo is about people who are falsely accused.  false accusations are the minority here, and the overwhelming majority of rapes go unreported. yet when those few do get reported, only a fraction of those actually go to trial, and only a fraction of those get jailed. now put in perspective a false accusation. if these people who are actual rapists don't get incarcerated, odds are an innocent person has the odds on their side.  now i don't want to downplay the monumental negative effect on someone's life that a false accusation would bring. but the fact that in almost every conversation about believing survivors there's always a couple people(usually men) who say "she's just doing it for attention", or "wow i guess everyone is a rapist, if they keep this up there'll be no one left" is not only disheartening but just plain ol' disgusting.  people are so willing to just let sexual assault slide because of the most ignorant reasons. "yeah he touched a little boy but have you seen house of cards? hes so good man it sucks that they fired him." "so what if he locked women in rooms so he can get naked and harass them, hes funny and thats no reason to cancel his shows." i am blown away with the lack of empathy that so many men show when they see a woman coming into the spotlight to tell her story, all because it messes with their favorite shows or movies. 
in summary believe survivors and stop whining

text:
meet @anxiety_inspiration
„Éª„Éª„Éª
my head feels foggy and a strange fast feeling comes over me. i get up quickly and try to shake it off of me. fuck , so uncomfortable! my heart beats so hard that i feel it throughout my body . shaking abit ! okay remember to breathe now . what did i think about now? can not remember thinking about something special. why do i feel like this ? am i getting crazy maybe ? it's the same feeling many get when they are sleeping and dreaming that they are falling and wake up directly when you hit the ground. (bam) like a shock ! i'm feeling that feeling, but i never hit the ground! the fear of something just goes on. feeling lightheaded and trying to find a comfortable position to fall asleep. thoughts are flying tonight . maybe its not anxiety this time? maybe i'm sick? of course i'm not sick. the anxiety plays with me! trying all the tools i have for working through the anxiety but nothing works . telling myself ive done the anxiety rush before , the panic attacks, ptsd flashbacks, ive done it all before and im still here . i will be fine ! tomorrow is a new day üí≠üå†
.

text: *mature content warning* i'm making this post to talk about my experience with sexual abuse, i won't go into too much detail. i felt i needed to say what i'm about to say because i should not have to keep quiet about what i went through.(this post is inspired by the brett kavanagh case) in my first real relationship (almost 2 years) there were many times i was forced or manipulated into doing things i repeatedly said no to. its crazy to think that while you're in a relationship for so long you don't clearly see the abuse but once you actually open your eyes and see what is going on you are able to take action and leave. i always just thought "well she still loves me i can let it slide this one time" (which led into several times). i have disabled comments on this post because i don't want sympathy or other comments. i made this post because i'm tired of being silent about it while people think this person is one way when they're not and they're doing just fine while i have permanent emotional scars. there is a link in my bio to a more detailed paper i wrote on what i went through. #empowerment #metoo #ibelieveher #ibelievechristineblaseyford #sexualabuse

text:
@ryan_gosling would be a no brainier for #mancrushmonday , but we here @moviesraisedus are going to go a bit deeper and choose his character "dean" from the @bluevalentinemovie . a man who is satisfied with a standard life and #loves his #wife and #child is betrayed by his cheating spouse and finds out the child isn't his. we find his complete #devotion as a #father and #husband totally and utterly #attractive . we also #love the fact that this #movie sheds light on the epidemic of #female douche bags. although we support the #metoo #movement and definitely feel that it's time for #men in #power to be held accountable for their despicable actions; we equally feel that the lower level of offenders have been #women (see: the majority of cases of #teachers having sex with students and most paternity lawsuits are because the #mother isn't positive of which man fathered her #baby ) and no one is addressing it. we have found that we've grown tired of the overuse of the stereotypical portrayal of men as poor father's, liers, and cheaters. just as we've grown tired of #action #movies where the protagonist gets 20 shots out of a 6 shot revolver before he runs out of bullets , defeats 100 men and comes out with 1 flesh wound, and never reloads anything!! we find it #refreshing to see a male portrayed as the more love struck #partner in the #relationship and the female as an unhappy cheating witch. if you haven't seen blue valentine and want something a little different from the norm, we highly recommend it! plus you get to see a #sexy #ryangosling .

#moviesraisedus #movielife #films #cinema

text:
the votive vulva vase:

this vase is more than just a mere vessel; within it, it holds all that it is to be feminine. 
all the fluidity of who and what we are; the surfaces that shaped us whether gently or abruptly. 
this vase holds all of our tears; whether otherworldly joy or deep seated despair. 
it holds the blood that was lost during the moments of our birth; it holds all the blood lost each and every time a child comes into existence... and it too holds the monthly loss of our blood when life has not formed. 
this vase holds all the wine that we have ingested; the times of jovial celebration that led to satiety as well as the times of reckless decadence, but on whose account? 
this vase is an ode to women, and all that we hold within.

text:
2 of 30. moments of gratitude.  well it must be working....this whole #grattitudepractice thing, or at the very least it‚Äôs giving me a reason to look for things to be grateful for. god forbid i say i‚Äôm gonna post for 30 days and screw or up on day two! lol! .
.
.
having spent the majority of my life only knowing ‚Äúconditional love‚Äù i‚Äôm very adept at giving others what they need to feel loved. less adept at receiving it. the words ‚Äúif you really loved me üçÉyou‚Äôd do what i say
üçÉ you‚Äôd believe what i believed
üçÉyou‚Äôd forgive and forget....all echo in my mind. the implication that the only way to receive love was to do the right thing, say the right words, behave the right way.  or that love would be taken away.  this is the narcissists way to keep you close. keep you needing them. keep you dancing like a marionette....jumping with every jerk of the string. .
.
but this is no way to live....no way to be alive.....no way to be free. .
.
today, as i‚Äôm showered in kisses from my doggies,  i am reminded of how far i‚Äôve come. how i‚Äôm learning to receive and give love freely. without the strings of a puppet master. they love me without question or expectation. to them i am worthy. no matter what. and for this i am grateful. .
.
.
.
.

text:
'as i finished the last book, i was thinking about all the men ‚Äì and many women ‚Äì who refuse to call themselves feminists. the writer bell hooks says that whenever she introduces herself as a feminist, people respond that feminists are lesbians who hate men and want to make life miserable for white men. when she then asks them about the feminist books they‚Äôve read, they go silent.

we need to ‚Äúcreate a mass-based educational movement to teach everyone about feminism‚Äù, hooks writes in feminism is for everybody, and i can‚Äôt stop thinking that this is what #metoo is.'
.
.
@carlcederstrom, how to be a good man: what i learned from a month reading the feminist classics (@guardian) #feministswithoutborders
.
.

text:
before, posting a photo like this would be easy. but it‚Äôs hard to look at this photo and see parts of me i don‚Äôt recognize anymore. i use to have this softness about me, this playfulness and feeling comfortable in my own skin. but because of him that part of me was stripped away. 
it started first with verbal abuse, wearing me down word by word. 
then the hit came; the force of his hand smashing across my face. more incidents happened and my fear of him grew bigger. i did leave but kept silent about the abuse. mainly because of fear but mostly because we were in the same circles of people through the work we did. i feared no one would believe me, it was my word against his. it was months later on that february 29th night that he finally broke my spirit. he came over to talk and something in him switched to pure darkness. with fists cocked he came at me with rage. all i could do was embrace for the hit. in a second i looked down to see my cat watching in fear and all i could think was is he going to kill me and arthur too? 
when i finally went to the police the officer told me to ‚Äúlet sleeping dogs lie‚Äù and to just move past it. for 2.5 years it has worn away at my spirt and trust in people. what that day did to me caused me to try taking my life months after it. there have been many low points over these two years that the thought of not being here seemed better than feeling the pain and fear that i did each day. some of the days it‚Äôs taken every thing i have to get out of bed. and on the days that aren‚Äôt as bad i try to celebrate the small wins that i am still here to tell my story and hopefully help someone else. 
then something bigger stepped in and created a space to have a conversation with 2 police officers. upon hearing my story with their support i went and refiled and told the full history of the abuse. it was the first time i heard a man in authority say ‚Äúyou know this isn‚Äôt your fault‚Äù. ptsd is debilitating and can leave you feeling paralyzed. there are tools out there to help but it isn‚Äôt always a simple solution to overcoming it.

text:
after dipping my toe back into the 90's i began to reflect on my eating habits and their relationship with my wallowing - and there was definitely a toxic one present!

keeping on track when life throws you curve balls is something i find super challenging and sometimes i feel like i use those tougher times as an excuse to let loose (when i know the best thing for me, personally, is routine). acknowledging this behavioural pattern was really the stepping stone to change but this chart is perfect for helping me take accountability.

it lives in my kitchen so i see nearly everytime i go into the living area. it was actually ali who came up with the idea for 5kg celebration incentives and this chart as a way to stay on track, which is slowly but surely aiding in the rachael downsize mish.

simple yet effective.

continued...
they say medication will help or at least control your symptoms but i still heard voices, i still saw things. the only difference was that i couldn‚Äôt react to the voices. at least if i can cut myself, i feel some kind of control, some kind of power. however, if i am sleeping for 18-20 hours of my life, what is the point of living?‚Äù ‚Äúso i kept stopping the medications and the voices were allowed to exist somewhere. they were powerful and overwhelming. one day, i finally decided to give in. i told myself ‚Äòi can‚Äôt fight them anymore as they are just going to harass me, so i am just going to give in to the voices.‚Äô i did and it brought me to where i am today. i had a set of bad voices telling me that they will kill me if i am going to pursue what i was. i also had another set of voices that i call good vampires. they were my angels because they protected me from the bad guys. life is about uncertainties. i think everyone deals with uncertainties by believing in another form of uncertainty. it is christ for one person, it is kali for somebody else, it is vampire for me. i believe life gave me schizophrenia to experience because i can make sense of it and share the same knowledge with the world. there are different ways to exist, schizophrenia is just one of them. i don‚Äôt see anything wrong with it.‚Äù co-founder of the red door.

text:
#sold
debra gindhart's artswalk 2018 exhibit "girl power" tells of influencing cultural attitudes and the transformation of stereotypes. there is no singular medium or style that unites feminist artists, they often combine aspects from various movements and media, including conceptual art, body art, and wearable art into works that presented a message about women's experience and the need for gender equality. gindhart uses aerosol paints and acrylics and assemblage technique pieces. 
feminist art creates opportunities for women and minority artists. paving the path for identity art and activist art. debra gindhart seeks to create a dialogue between the viewer and the artwork through the inclusion of women's perspective on issues of human trafficking, me too movement, ecology, gun control, and more. 
art is not merely an object for aesthetic admiration, but also incites the viewer to question the social and political landscape, and through this questioning, possibly affect the world and incite change toward equality. 
debra gindhart's trafficked art, real babes recycle, armed & polite, #metoo series, and degradation  dolls will highlight her artswalk 2018 exhibit. she will also have her green glam studio collection of haute couture hangers featured in her artist show and reception.

before feminism feminist artists often embraced alternative media, incorporating fabric, fiber, and performance, as these materials did not have the same historically male-dominated precedent that painting and sculpture carried. by using these non-traditional media, they sought to expand the definition of fine arts to include a wider variety of media and artistic perspectives.

please join debra in her gindhart at madjax second floor studio/gallery for artswalk 2018 meet and greet the artist while enjoying light refreshments.
